What you need to know:

In November 2019, cultural and religious leaders from at least 20 communities with high rates of FGM signed a declaration to end the practice.Overall, three per cent of Kenyan girls under the age of 15 have undergone the cut.Unless the entire society is educated and anti-FGM messages are redesigned, nothing will change.The Kuria community has four clans, with each circumcising its girls in an annual rotation.